{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017aqRwRopH78uyUHdbMS37p","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→I want to add a new TUI feature to add a devcontainer.json + startup scripts to a worktree or primary project branch\n     2→\n     3→- New command to create .devcontainer folder + artifacts if it doesn't exist. Same rules as other features, only show command if .devcontainer folder isn't already there. Also if targetting a worktree and primary has an existing .devcontainer folder, copy it instead of creating. Only addition will be the bind mount mentioned in next bullet\n     4→- Worktree branches will need an additional bind-mount to be added to mount the .git directory from the primary branch location. e.g.\n     5→  \"source=${localWorkspaceFolder}/../../my-project/.git,target=${localWorkspaceFolder}/../../my-project/.git,type=bind,consistency=cached\" . Should already be some utils in the codebase for figuring out primary branch location relative to worktree branch, but may need new ones\n     6→- Primary branches will already get the .git folder as part of the project mount. Nothing to add here\n     7→\n     8→## .devcontainer folder\n     9→\n    10→- .gitignore - use \\* to exclude everything in this folder\n    11→- setup.sh, setup-bash.sh, setup-agents.sh - same as in .devcontainers folder of this project\n    12→- devcontainer.json\n    13→\n    14→```jsonc\n    15→// For format details, see https://aka.ms/devcontainer.json. For config options, see the\n    16→// README at: https://github.com/devcontainers/templates/tree/main/src/ubuntu\n    17→{\n    18→  \"name\": \"Ubuntu\",\n    19→  // Or use a Dockerfile or Docker Compose file. More info: https://containers.dev/guide/dockerfile\n    20→  \"image\": \"mcr.microsoft.com/devcontainers/base:noble\",\n    21→  \"features\": {\n    22→    \"ghcr.io/devcontainers/features/node:1\": {\n    23→      \"nodeGypDependencies\": true,\n    24→      \"version\": \"latest\",\n    25→      \"pnpmVersion\": \"none\",\n    26→      \"nvmVersion\": \"latest\",\n    27→    },\n    28→  },\n    29→  \"mounts\": [\n    30→    // Bind-mount the primary .git directory since we are in a worktree\n    31→    // <PLACEHOLDER-FOR-WORKTREE-GIT-FOLDER>\n    32→\n    33→    // Isolated Claude settings per container\n    34→    \"source=claude-code-config-${devcontainerId},target=/home/vscode/.claude,type=volume\",\n    35→\n    36→    // Bind-mount .claude.json so login persists across rebuilds\n    37→    \"source=${localEnv:HOME}/.claude.json,target=/home/vscode/.claude.json,type=bind,consistency=cached\",\n    38→\n    39→    // Bind-mount skills from host into project directory for easier debugging of skills.\n    40→    // Can remove the `readonly` setting if you want to edit them from the container\n    41→    \"source=${localEnv:HOME}/.agents/skills,target=${containerWorkspaceFolder}/.claude/skills,type=bind,consistency=cached,readonly\",\n    42→  ],\n    43→  \"postCreateCommand\": \".devcontainer/setup.sh\",\n    44→  \"customizations\": {\n    45→    \"vscode\": {\n    46→      \"extensions\": [\n    47→        \"anthropic.claude-code\",\n    48→        \"dbaeumer.vscode-eslint\",\n    49→        \"esbenp.prettier-vscode\",\n    50→      ],\n    51→\n    52→      \"settings\": {\n    53→        // \"Yolo\" permissions for Claude\n    54→        \"claudeCode.allowDangerouslySkipPermissions\": true,\n    55→        \"claudeCode.initialPermissionMode\": \"bypassPermissions\",\n    56→\n    57→        // Copilot settings\n    58→        \"chat.agent.maxRequests\": 50,\n    59→        \"chat.tools.terminal.autoApprove\": {\n    60→          \"/.*/\": true,\n    61→        },\n    62→        \"chat.tools.terminal.ignoreDefaultAutoApproveRules\": true,\n    63→\n    64→        \"editor.defaultFormatter\": \"esbenp.prettier-vscode\",\n    65→        \"editor.formatOnSave\": true,\n    66→        \"terminal.integrated.defaultProfile.linux\": \"bash\",\n    67→        \"workbench.colorCustomizations\": {\n    68→          \"statusBar.background\": \"#7f3a57\",\n    69→          \"statusBar.foreground\": \"#ffffff\",\n    70→          \"titleBar.activeBackground\": \"#7f3a57\",\n    71→          \"titleBar.activeForeground\": \"#ffffff\",\n    72→          \"titleBar.inactiveBackground\": \"#7f5567\",\n    73→        },\n    74→      },\n    75→    },\n    76→  },\n    77→}\n    78→```\n    79→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d60ba2b-3510-499e-9789-87e948099be6","uuid":"b78e3a57-206f-4f36-814b-4fb5e42927bb","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/vscode-dashboard/_ignore/DESIGN.md","content":"I want to add a new TUI feature to add a devcontainer.json + startup scripts to a worktree or primary project branch\n\n- New command to create .devcontainer folder + artifacts if it doesn't exist. Same rules as other features, only show command if .devcontainer folder isn't already there. Also if targetting a worktree and primary has an existing .devcontainer folder, copy it instead of creating. Only addition will be the bind mount mentioned in next bullet\n- Worktree branches will need an additional bind-mount to be added to mount the .git directory from the primary branch location. e.g.\n  \"source=${localWorkspaceFolder}/../../my-project/.git,target=${localWorkspaceFolder}/../../my-project/.git,type=bind,consistency=cached\" . Should already be some utils in the codebase for figuring out primary branch location relative to worktree branch, but may need new ones\n- Primary branches will already get the .git folder as part of the project mount. Nothing to add here\n\n## .devcontainer folder\n\n- .gitignore - use \\* to exclude everything in this folder\n- setup.sh, setup-bash.sh, setup-agents.sh - same as in .devcontainers folder of this project\n- devcontainer.json\n\n```jsonc\n// For format details, see https://aka.ms/devcontainer.json. For config options, see the\n// README at: https://github.com/devcontainers/templates/tree/main/src/ubuntu\n{\n  \"name\": \"Ubuntu\",\n  // Or use a Dockerfile or Docker Compose file. More info: https://containers.dev/guide/dockerfile\n  \"image\": \"mcr.microsoft.com/devcontainers/base:noble\",\n  \"features\": {\n    \"ghcr.io/devcontainers/features/node:1\": {\n      \"nodeGypDependencies\": true,\n      \"version\": \"latest\",\n      \"pnpmVersion\": \"none\",\n      \"nvmVersion\": \"latest\",\n    },\n  },\n  \"mounts\": [\n    // Bind-mount the primary .git directory since we are in a worktree\n    // <PLACEHOLDER-FOR-WORKTREE-GIT-FOLDER>\n\n    // Isolated Claude settings per container\n    \"source=claude-code-config-${devcontainerId},target=/home/vscode/.claude,type=volume\",\n\n    // Bind-mount .claude.json so login persists across rebuilds\n    \"source=${localEnv:HOME}/.claude.json,target=/home/vscode/.claude.json,type=bind,consistency=cached\",\n\n    // Bind-mount skills from host into project directory for easier debugging of skills.\n    // Can remove the `readonly` setting if you want to edit them from the container\n    \"source=${localEnv:HOME}/.agents/skills,target=${containerWorkspaceFolder}/.claude/skills,type=bind,consistency=cached,readonly\",\n  ],\n  \"postCreateCommand\": \".devcontainer/setup.sh\",\n  \"customizations\": {\n    \"vscode\": {\n      \"extensions\": [\n        \"anthropic.claude-code\",\n        \"dbaeumer.vscode-eslint\",\n        \"esbenp.prettier-vscode\",\n      ],\n\n      \"settings\": {\n        // \"Yolo\" permissions for Claude\n        \"claudeCode.allowDangerouslySkipPermissions\": true,\n        \"claudeCode.initialPermissionMode\": \"bypassPermissions\",\n\n        // Copilot settings\n        \"chat.agent.maxRequests\": 50,\n        \"chat.tools.terminal.autoApprove\": {\n          \"/.*/\": true,\n        },\n        \"chat.tools.terminal.ignoreDefaultAutoApproveRules\": true,\n\n        \"editor.defaultFormatter\": \"esbenp.prettier-vscode\",\n        \"editor.formatOnSave\": true,\n        \"terminal.integrated.defaultProfile.linux\": \"bash\",\n        \"workbench.colorCustomizations\": {\n          \"statusBar.background\": \"#7f3a57\",\n          \"statusBar.foreground\": \"#ffffff\",\n          \"titleBar.activeBackground\": \"#7f3a57\",\n          \"titleBar.activeForeground\": \"#ffffff\",\n          \"titleBar.inactiveBackground\": \"#7f5567\",\n        },\n      },\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n","numLines":79,"startLine":1,"totalLines":79}}}
